obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (47653)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00027_195947_1517807321690&sectionId=47653&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00027_195947_1517807321690
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `This Act may be called the Rajasthan and Madhya Pradesh (Transfer of Territories)`
  line `Act, 1959.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (47654)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00027_195947_1517807321690&sectionId=47654&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00027_195947_1517807321690
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,—`
  line
  line `(a) "appointed day" means the 1st day of October, 1959;`
  line
  line `(b) "assembly constituency", "council constituency" and "parliamentary constituency" have the`
  line `same meanings as in the Representation of the People Act, 1950 (43 of 1950);`
  line
  line `(c) "sitting member", in relation to either House of Parliament or of the Legislature of a State,`
  line `means a person who, immediately before the appointed day, is a member of that House;`
  line
  line `(d) "transferred territories" means the territories specified in the First Schedule and transferred`
  line `from the State of Rajasthan to the State of Madhya Pradesh by section 3.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (47655)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Transfer of territories from Rajasthan to Madhya Pradesh.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00027_195947_1517807321690&sectionId=47655&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00027_195947_1517807321690
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) As from the appointed day,`
  line `there shall be added to the State of Madhya Pradesh the territories specified in the First Schedule which`
  line `shall thereupon cease to form part of the State of Rajasthan.`
  line
  line `(2) The transferred territories shall be included in, and form part of Bhanpura pargana of, Mandsaur`
  line `district in the State of Madhya Pradesh.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in sub-section (2) shall be deemed to affect the power of the State Government to alter`
  line `after the appointed day the name, extent or boundaries of any district in the State of Madhya Pradesh.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (47656)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Amendment of the First Schedule to the Constitution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00027_195947_1517807321690&sectionId=47656&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00027_195947_1517807321690
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `As from the appointed day, in the First`
  line `Schedule to the Constitution, under the heading "I. THE STATES",—`
  line
  line `(a) in the entry against "6. Madhya Pradesh", after the words and figures "States Reorganisation`
  line `Act, 1956", the words, brackets and figures "and the First Schedule to the Rajasthan and Madhya`
  line `Pradesh (Transfer of Territories) Act, 1959" shall be inserted.`
  line
  line `(b) in the entry against "11. Rajasthan", after the words and figures "States Reorganisation`
  line `Act, 1956", the words, brackets and figures "but excluding the territories specified in the First`
  line `Schedule to the Rajasthan and Madhya Pradesh (Transfer of Territories) Act, 1959" shall be inserted.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (47657)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Amendments of Delimitation Orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00027_195947_1517807321690&sectionId=47657&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00027_195947_1517807321690
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `The Delimitation of Parliamentary and Assembly`
  line `Constituencies Order, 1956, and the Constitution of Council Constituencies (Madhya Pradesh)`
  line `Order, 1957, shall have effect subject to the modifications specified in the Second Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (47658)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Provision as to sitting members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00027_195947_1517807321690&sectionId=47658&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00027_195947_1517807321690
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The sitting members of the House of the People`
  line `representing Mandsaur constituency in the State of Madhya Pradesh and Kotah constituency in the State`
  line `of Rajasthan shall, notwithstanding the alteration in the extent of those constituencies by virtue of the`
  line `provisions of this Act, continue to be members of the House of the People.`
  line
  line `(2) The sitting members of the Legislative Assemblies of Madhya Pradesh and Rajasthan representing`
  line `Growth constituency and Begun constituency respectively shall, notwithstanding the alteration in the`
  line `extent of those constituencies by virtue of the provisions of this Act, continue to be members of the said`
  line Assemblies.
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (47659)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Extension of jurisdiction of Madhya Pradesh High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00027_195947_1517807321690&sectionId=47659&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00027_195947_1517807321690
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) As from the appointed day,—`
  line
  line `(a) the jurisdiction of the High Court of Madhya Pradesh shall extend to the transferred`
  line `territories; and`
  line
  line `(b) the High Court of Rajasthan shall have no jurisdiction in respect of the said territories.`
  line
  line `(2) If, immediately before the appointed day, there is any proceeding relatable to the transferred`
  line `territories pending in the High Court of Rajasthan, then, notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `sub-section (1), such proceeding shall be heard and disposed of by that High Court.`
  line
  line `(3) Any order made by the High Court of Rajasthan in any proceeding with respect to which that`
  line `High Court exercises jurisdiction by virtue of sub-section (2), shall, for all purposes, have effect, not only`
  line `as an order of the High Court of Rajasthan, but also as an order made by the High Court of Madhya`
  line Pradesh.
  line
  line `(4) For the purposes of this section,—`
  line
  line `(a) proceedings shall be deemed to be pending in the High Court of Rajasthan until that Court has`
  line `disposed of all issues between the parties, including any issues with respect to the taxation of the`
  line `costs of the proceedings and shall include appeals, applications for leave to appeal to the Supreme`
  line `Court, applications for review, petitions for revision and petitions for writs;`
  line
  line `(b) references to a High Court shall be construed as including references to a Judge or Division`
  line `Court thereof, and references to an order made by a Court or a Judge shall be construed as including`
  line `references to a sentence, judgment or decree passed or made by that Court or Judge.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (47670)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Appropriation of moneys for expenditure in transferred territories under existing Appropriation Acts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00027_195947_1517807321690&sectionId=47670&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00027_195947_1517807321690
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `As from the appointed day, any Act passed by the Legislature of Madhya Pradesh`
  line `before that day for the appropriation of any money out of the Consolidated Fund of the State to meet any`
  line `expenditure in respect of any part of the financial year 1959-60 shall have effect also in relation to the`
  line `transferred territories, and it shall be lawful for the State Government to spend any amount for those`
  line `territories out of the amount authorised by such Act to be expended for any services in that State.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (47661)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Assets and liabilities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00027_195947_1517807321690&sectionId=47661&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00027_195947_1517807321690
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) All land and all stores, articles and other goods in the transferred`
  line `territories belonging to the State of Rajasthan shall, as from the appointed day, pass to the State of`
  line `Madhya Pradesh.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—In this sub-section, the expression "land" includes immoveable property of every kind`
  line `and any rights in or over such property and the expression "goods" does not include coins, bank notes and`
  line `currency notes.`
  line
  line `(2) All rights, liabilities and obligations, whether arising out of a contract or otherwise, of the State of`
  line `Rajasthan in relation to the transferred territories shall, as from the appointed day, be the rights, liabilities`
  line `and obligations, respectively, of the State of Madhya Pradesh.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (47662)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `State Financial Corporations and State Electricity Boards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00027_195947_1517807321690&sectionId=47662&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00027_195947_1517807321690
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `As from the appointed day,—`
  line
  line `(a) the Financial Corporations constituted under the State Financial Corporations`
  line `Act, 1951 (63 of 1951), for the States of Rajasthan and Madhya Pradesh, and`
  line
  line `(b) the State Electricity Boards constituted under the Electricity (Supply) Act, 1948 (54 of 1948),`
  line `for the said States,`
  line
  line `shall be deemed to have been constituted for those States with their areas as altered by the provisions of`
  line `section 3.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (47663)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Extension of laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00027_195947_1517807321690&sectionId=47663&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00027_195947_1517807321690
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `All laws which immediately before the appointed day extend to, or are in`
  line `force in, the Mandsaur district in the State of Madhya Pradesh but do not extend to, or are not in force in,`
  line `the transferred territories shall, as from that day, extend to, or as the case may be, come into force in, the`
  line `transferred territories; and all laws which, immediately before the appointed day, are in force in the`
  line `transferred territories, but not in the Mandsaur district in the State of Madhya Pradesh, shall, on that day,`
  line `cease to be in force in the transferred territories, except as respects things done or omitted to be done`
  line `before that day.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—In this section "law" includes any enactment, ordinance, regulation, order, bye-law,`
  line `rule, scheme, notification or other instrument having the force of law in the whole or in any part of`
  line `Madhya Pradesh or Rajasthan.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (47664)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Power to construe laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00027_195947_1517807321690&sectionId=47664&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00027_195947_1517807321690
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Any court, tribunal or authority required or empowered to enforce any`
  line `law extended to the transferred territories by section 11 may, for the purpose of facilitating its application`
  line `in relation to the transferred territories, construe the law in such manner, without affecting the substance,`
  line `as may be necessary or proper in regard to the matter before the court, tribunal or authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (47665)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Legal proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00027_195947_1517807321690&sectionId=47665&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00027_195947_1517807321690
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Where, immediately before the appointed day, the State of Rajasthan is a`
  line `party to any legal proceedings with respect to any property, rights or liabilities transferred to the State of`
  line `Madhya Pradesh under this Act, that State shall be deemed to be substituted for the State of Rajasthan as a`
  line `party to those proceedings, or added as a party thereto, as the case may be, and the proceedings may`
  line `continue accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (47666)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Transfer of pending proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00027_195947_1517807321690&sectionId=47666&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00027_195947_1517807321690
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every proceeding pending immediately before the`
  line `appointed day before any court (other than a High Court), tribunal, authority or officer in any area which`
  line `on that day falls within the State of Rajasthan shall, if it is a proceeding relating exclusively to any part of`
  line `the transferred territories, stand transferred to the corresponding court, tribunal, authority or officer in the`
  line `State of Madhya Pradesh.`
  line
  line `(2) If any question arises as to whether any proceeding should stand transferred under sub-section (1),`
  line `it shall be referred to the High Court of Rajasthan and the decision of that High Court shall be final.`
  line
  line `(3) In this section,—`
  line
  line `(a) "proceeding" includes any suit, case or appeal; and`
  line
  line `(b) "corresponding court, tribunal, authority or officer" in Madhya Pradesh means—`
  line
  line `(i) the court, tribunal, authority or officer in which, or before whom, the proceeding would`
  line `have lain if the proceeding had been instituted after the appointed day, or`
  line
  line `(ii) in case of doubt, such court, tribunal, authority or officer in that State as may be`
  line `determined after the appointed day by the Government of Madhya Pradesh, or before the`
  line `appointed day by the Government of Rajasthan, to be the corresponding court, tribunal, authority`
  line `or officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (47667)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Effect of provisions inconsistent with other laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00027_195947_1517807321690&sectionId=47667&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00027_195947_1517807321690
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall have effect`
  line `notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (47668)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00027_195947_1517807321690&sectionId=47668&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00027_195947_1517807321690
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this`
  line `Act (including any difficulty in relation to the transition under section 11 from one law to another law),`
  line `the President may by order do anything not inconsistent with any such provision which appears to him to`
  line `be necessary for the purpose of removing the difficulty.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (47669)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1986, s. 2 and the Schedule, for certain words (w.e.f. 15-5-1986)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00027_195947_1517807321690&sectionId=47669&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00027_195947_1517807321690
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central "Government may, by notification the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to give effect to the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every rule made under this section shall be laid as soon as may be after it is made before each`
  line `House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or ^1[in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid] both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be, so however that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_translations:
  hi obj_root_law_translations_hi
